hands_on_practices.solution:
We have 
$$E_{\rm sym}(n_b,x_p)=S(n_b)\,(1-2x_p)^2,\quad P_{\rm sym}=n_b^2\frac{\partial E_{\rm sym}}{\partial n_b}\Big|_{x_p}\,. $$ 
Hence 
$$P_{\rm sym}=n_b^2\,(1-2x_p)^2\,\frac{dS}{dn_b}\,. $$ 
With 
$$S(n_b)=\frac{1}{3}E_{F,0}+\!S_{pot,0}\Bigl(\frac{n_b}{n_s}\Bigr)^\gamma,\quad E_{F,0}=\frac{\hbar^2}{2m}\Bigl(\frac{3\pi^2n_b}{2}\Bigr)^{\!2/3},$$ 
we find 
$$\frac{dS}{dn_b}
=\frac{1}{3}\frac{dE_{F,0}}{dn_b}
+\!S_{pot,0}\,\gamma\Bigl(\frac{n_b}{n_s}\Bigr)^{\gamma-1}\frac{1}{n_s}\,. $$ 
Since 
$$\frac{dE_{F,0}}{dn_b}
=\frac{\hbar^2}{2m}\frac{2}{3}\Bigl(\frac{3\pi^2}{2}\Bigr)^{\!2/3}n_b^{-1/3}
=\frac{\hbar^2}{3m}\Bigl(\frac{3\pi^2}{2}\Bigr)^{\!2/3}n_b^{-1/3},$$ 
we obtain 
$$\frac{dS}{dn_b}
=\frac{\hbar^2}{9m}\Bigl(\frac{3\pi^2}{2}\Bigr)^{\!2/3}n_b^{-1/3}
+S_{pot,0}\,\frac{\gamma}{n_s}\Bigl(\frac{n_b}{n_s}\Bigr)^{\gamma-1}\!. $$ 
Therefore 
$$P_{\rm sym}
=n_b^2\,(1-2x_p)^2\!\biggl[
\frac{\hbar^2}{9m}\Bigl(\frac{3\pi^2}{2}\Bigr)^{\!2/3}n_b^{-1/3}
+S_{pot,0}\,\frac{\gamma}{n_s}\Bigl(\frac{n_b}{n_s}\Bigr)^{\gamma-1}
\biggr].$$ 
Rewriting $n_b^2n_b^{-1/3}=n_b^{5/3}$ and $n_b^2(n_b/n_s)^{\gamma-1}/n_s=n_b^{\gamma+1}/n_s^\gamma$ gives the final form below.
